  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Remote Capacity Building of Iraqi, Syrian and Yemeni NGOs to Adapt to COVID-19 Context</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The core of the project is provision of remote mentoring and coaching, based on the capacity building needs assessment of respective NGOs. The mentoring and coaching is based on the existing online resources for organizational strengthening/ adjustment to COVID-19 as well as COVID-19 response.


HAD will provide urgent capacity development to frontline local NGOs in Iraq, Syria and Yemen. The project is planned to be implemented over the course of 3 months. 


The project is to enable the frontline NGOs to (i) adapt to COVID-19 and carry on with their programmes, (ii) implement COVID-19 interventions with the local populations. To this extent, all project activities focus on strengthening NGOs capacities.</narrative>
  </description>
